						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up to the right of the Sōmēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1278.</p>						

						<p>This record, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">14th century A.D.,</hi> is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Īsvara, Dvitīya-Phālguṇa, śu. 14, Tuesday.</hi> In this century the details of the date correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1278, March 8, Tuesday f.d.t. ·75.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records the death of Chika, son of Gōyanāyaka, who was the household officer <hi rend="italic">(mane-adhikāri)</hi> of Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara <hi rend="bold">Śāḷuveya Ballugidēva-Rāṇeya,</hi> in a fight with a certain <hi rend="italic">rāhuta.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
